<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-0196 </DOCNO><TEXT>Basic research on coal was restarted in France from the years 1978-80onwards, by creation of inter-laboratory Team Groups called GRECO orGS according to their links with industry. Coal pyrolysis was one ofthe main themes to be developed. The characterization of solid and liquidproducts from coal pyrolysis was presented at the International Symposiumof CNRS held in Metz from 3rd to 6th November 1987. This article is anintroduction to the topics discussed during this Symposium, a short presentationof the works presented, especially of the Plenary Lectures, a summaryof the discussions held at the Round Tables organized during the Seminar.14 refs.</TEXT></DOC>